description: TEHRAN – Multiple Iranian officials have warned in separate remarks that Tehran is prepared to launch more attacks against Israel if the regime responds to Operation True Promise II, which came in retaliation for the regime's assassination of multiple high-ranking Resistance officials and commanders in the past two months.
title: Iran says more military action on the way if Israel does not back down

description: TEHRAN- Israel has been driven into a corner as regional resistance groups intensify attacks against the regime in the wake of Iran’s ballistic missile salvo on Tel Aviv.
title: Stormy skies ahead: Israel faces unprecedented resistance

description: TEHRAN- Iranians were not the only ones celebrating Tehran’s retaliatory missile strikes against the Israeli regime. The joyous mood quickly spread to other countries as well.
title: Celebrations in West Asia and beyond follow Iran’s missile strike

description: TEHRAN – On Wednesday morning, October 2, 2024, just hours after Iran launched its second retaliatory strike against Israel, the world watched in stunned silence. The “True Promise II” operation, as it was officially dubbed, saw Iran’s Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) unleash over 180 ballistic and hypersonic missiles on multiple Israeli military targets in occupied Palestine.
title: “I am deeply mourning”, or in other words, It’s Far from Over!

description: Israeli Foreign Minister Israel Katz on October 2 declared UN Secretary-General Antonio Guterres “persona non grata” and barred him from entering Israel, claiming Guterres had not “unequivocally” condemned Iran's retaliatory attack, The Cradle reported.
title: Israel declares UN chief 'persona non grata'

description: Dozens of Palestinians were killed as Israel stepped up its military operations across Gaza.

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s minister of foreign affairs has appointed Esmaeil Baghaei as the new head of the Public Diplomacy Center and spokesperson for the Iranian foreign ministry.

description: TEHRAN – The sons of the Leader of the Islamic Revolution visited the Hezbollah Resistance movement’s office in Tehran on Tuesday to deliver Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei’s message of condolence.
title: Leader's sons visit Hezbollah office in Tehran with Ayatollah Khamenei’s message

description: TEHRAN - In a note, Keyhan addressed the IRGC's missile attack on the Zionist regime and wrote: The existence of the usurping regime was targeted on Tuesday night and the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps shattered the Zionist regime’s absurd dignity.
title: IRGC shatters Israel's absurd dignity

description: TEHRAN – Iran's Foreign Minister, Abbas Araqchi, announced on Wednesday that the Islamic Republic's retaliatory operation against Israel has officially concluded; however, he warned that any counter-response by the Israeli regime would provoke an even more intense reaction from Tehran.
title: More severe response awaits Israel in case of escalation of conflicts: Iran FM

description: TEHRAN-The Persian translation of the novel “The Castle of Otranto” written by Horace Walpole has been released in the Iranian book market.

description: TEHRAN – After two months of waiting and pursuing legal and political avenues to redress the Zionist regime's violation of its rights in the assassination of former Hamas leader Ismail Haniyeh in Tehran, Iran launched Operation True Promise II.
title: Iran ready for any scenario

description: MADRID – Finally, following various speculations in political and media circles about how Tehran would respond to the series of assassinations carried out by Israel, Iran launched a second direct attack on the occupied territories from its own territory around 8:00 PM on Tuesday.
title: An analysis of Operation 'True Promise II'

description: TEHRAN – Salvos of Iranian missiles rained on the occupied territories on Tuesday night, comforting the people of the region who were eagerly awaiting a response to Israel’s terror attacks in the past two months, and occupying observers with the thought of what could happen next.
title: Iran's Hand on the Trigger

description: TEHRAN – Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei will reportedly perform this week’s Friday prayers in Tehran.
title: Ayatollah Khamenei to lead this week’s Friday prayers

description: BEIRUT- Netanyahu and his cabinet appear to be riding a wave of high confidence following their intensified bombardment of Lebanon. They operate under the assumption that relentless strikes can dismantle the Islamic resistance in Lebanon before it can effectively respond and stabilize internally. This strategy has bolstered Netanyahu’s popularity within the entity, including among opposition members.
title: The sudden response

description: TEHRAN- Iran launched approximately 200 ballistic missiles at Israeli positions in the occupied territories on October 1, targeting three military bases near Tel Aviv. The attack dubbed Operation True Promise II came in response to Israel’s assassinations of top Resistance leaders including Hezbollah Secretary-general Sayyad Hassan Nasrallah and Hamas political chief Ismail Haniyeh. This was Iran’s second attack against Iran after launching drones and missiles at the occupied territories in April.
title: Operation True Promise II
